This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it introduces an acceleration for covariance matrix adaptation evolution strategies (CMA-ES), which is a popular optimization algorithm in the field of evolutionary computation. Additionally, the paper proposes improvements to the default parameter setting in CMA-ES, which is a common topic in the field of optimization. 

The paper also discusses the use of active CMA to guarantee positive definiteness of the covariance matrix, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

The paper's focus on optimization and parameter tuning also makes it relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's use of numerical experiments and analysis of algorithm performance makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
